.TH "generic_setlease" 9 "generic_setlease" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
generic_setlease \- sets a lease on an open file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" generic_setlease
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "long arg "  ","
.BI "struct file_lock **flp "  ","
.BI "void **priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
file pointer
.IP "arg" 12
type of lease to obtain
.IP "flp" 12
input - file_lock to use, output - file_lock inserted
.IP "priv" 12
private data for lm_setup (may be NULL if lm_setup
doesn't require it)

The (input) flp->fl_lmops->lm_break function is required
by \fBbreak_lease\fP.
